OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBrits most likely to say   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25F'we don't live to work'    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Dean Holden is one of many people      
OL,6, thinking there is more to life than    
OL,7, work, hanging up his mic as a railway  
OL,8, station announcer after 16 years.      
OL,10,F"Life is too short. That's always been 
OL,11,Fmy saying - live it," he told the BBC. 
OL,13,FHis early retirement comes as a study  
OL,14,Fsuggests people in the UK today are    
OL,15,Fmore likely to say it would be a good  
OL,16,Fthing if less importance was placed on 
OL,17,Fwork than they were 40 years ago.      
OL,19,FThey are also among the least likely to
OL,20,Fsay work should always come first.     
